			<item>
				<title>Another update</title>
				<link>/blog/another-update/</link>
				<pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>/blog/another-update/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;This is another example article. Each article lives in its own Markdown file, which keeps writing separate from the design of the website.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;publishing-a-new-post&#34;&gt;Publishing a new post&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Create a new file in &lt;code&gt;content/blog&lt;/code&gt;, add a title, date, and description at the top, then write the article below it. The blog list will automatically show the newest posts first.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>My first article</title>
				<link>/blog/my-first-article/</link>
				<pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>/blog/my-first-article/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;This is the first post in my blog. I will use this space to document the work I do, the questions I explore, and the lessons I learn along the way.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-i-want-to-share&#34;&gt;What I want to share&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Some posts will be short progress notes; others may be deeper write-ups of a project, a competition, or a topic I am studying. The goal is to make the process as useful as the final result.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
